# std/process imports and runs on the interpreter

Guard: `ProcessOptions`' default `Map.empty` crashed the whole module at
import ("No method 'empty' on NativeFnV(<native:Map>)") — std/process was
unusable from `.ssc` on the interpreter (found by busi's sites-as-files
git-backup slice).

[exec, ProcessOptions, ProcessResult](std/process.ssc)

```scalascript
val r = exec("echo", List("process-ok"), ProcessOptions(None, Map(), None))
println(r.stdout.trim())
println(r.exitCode)
```
